text: Pål Fjelde (born 26 July 1994) is a Norwegian footballer who plays as a midfielder for Bryne 07 Vestur in the Faroe Islands Premier League. Fjelde has previously played for Norwegian clubs Viking and Bryne, and had a brief spell with Scottish Championship side St Mirren and had a brief spell with Faroe Islands Premier League side 07 Vestur . ==Career== Born in Jørpeland, Fjelde started his career in Staal Jørpeland IL. He made his league debut as a substitute against Stabæk in June 2014. On 20 November 2014 he signed for Norwegian First Division side Bryne. On 12 January 2017, Fjelde transferred to Scottish Championship side St Mirren, signing with the club until the end of the 2016–17 season. Fjelde left the club at the end of his contract, having made seven appearances for the Buddies. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:People from Strand, Norway Category:Norwegian footballers Category:Viking FK players Category:Eliteserien players Category:Bryne FK players Category:St Mirren F.C. players Category:Norwegian First Division players Category:Association football defenders Category:Norwegian expatriate footballers Category:Expatriate footballers in Scotland Category:Norwegian expatriate sportspeople in Scotland Category:Scottish Professional Football League players
